LEVEL 3 — Web App (Streamlit)


Features
- Interactive UI
- User inputs (sliders)
- Real-time prediction
- Displays graphs


1. Interactive UI
A user-friendly interface where users can interact instead of using the terminal.
What happens:
- Opens a web app (using Streamlit)
- Shows buttons, sliders, text, results

Why is it important:
- Makes your project easy to use
- Looks professional on GitHub


2. User Inputs (Sliders)
Users provide input values using sliders.
What happens:
- Select study hours (e.g., 0–12)
- Select attendance (0–100%)
- Select previous score

Example:
Study Hours: 7  
Attendance: 85  
Score: 75

Why is it important:
- Simple and intuitive input method
- No typing errors


3. Real-Time Prediction
The model instantly predicts based on user input.
What happens:
- User clicks “Predict”
- Model processes input
- Shows result immediately

Output:
PASS
or
FAIL

Why is it important:
- Fast response
- Feels like a real application


4. Displays Graphs
Shows visual insights inside the app.
What happens:
- Displays heatmap, scatter plot, etc.
- Helps users understand data patterns

Why is it important:
- Makes app more informative
- Improves presentation quality
